void onTransactionApproved(Transaction transaction)

Parameters:

Since:
2.0.0

onTransactionDeclined

void onTransactionDeclined(Transaction transaction)
Declined handler for the execution of a transaction. At this stage the transaction is completely executed but was declined.

2.0.0

onTransactionAborted

void onTransactionAborted(Transaction transaction)
Aborted handler for the execution of a transaction. At this stage the shopper or merchant has aborted the transaction.

Parameters:
transaction - The aborted transaction.
Since:
2.0.0

onTransactionFailure

void onTransactionFailure(Transaction transaction,
                          MposError error)
Failure handler for the execution of a transaction. There are different reasons why a transaction may fail: Network errors, missing parameters, invalid payment details). Some of those errors are recoverable (e.g. by just starting the transaction again). The error will provider information about the recoverability.

Parameters:
transaction - The failed transaction.
error - Indicates what happened and how to proceed
Since:
2.0.0

onTransactionActionRequired

void onTransactionActionRequired(Transaction transaction,
                                 TransactionAction action,
                                 TransactionActionSupport supportData)
Action handler for a transaction, used to request additional details when needed (e.g. some POS transaction needs a customer signature). To only get requests for actions that you support, provide a bit mask of actions when initializing the provider.

Parameters:
transaction - The transaction requesting the additional action/data
action - The requested action/data
supportData - Additional data that may be needed for certain types of actions (will require a downcast)
Since:
2.0.0
